<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1430,593,1017]" box="[223,909,666,690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Diagnosis: 
<bibRefCitation author="Loginova" box="[349,554,666,690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Loginova, M. M. (1964 b) Podotrjad Psyllinea. In: G. Y. Bei-Bienko (Ed), Opredelitel' nasekomykh Evropeiskoi chasti SSSR. Izdatel'stvo &quot; Nauka &quot;, Moscow, Russia, pp. 437 - 482." type="book chapter" year="1964" yearSuffix="b">
Loginova (
<number box="[472,531,666,690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1964.0">1964</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Brown" box="[566,905,666,690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Brown, R. G. &amp; Hodkinson, I. D. (1988) Taxonomy and ecology of the jumping plant-lice of Panama (Homoptera: Psylloidea) (Entomonograph 9). E. J. Brill / Scandinavian Science Press Ltd., Leiden, 304 pp." type="book" year="1988">
Brown and Hodkinson (
<number box="[835,896,666,690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1988.0">1988</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1430,593,1017]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Internal relationships: Five tribes are recognised (
<bibRefCitation author="White" box="[773,1070,703,727]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="White, I. M. &amp; Hodkinson, I. D. (1985) Nymphal taxonomy and systematics of Psylloidea (Homoptera). Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Entomology, 50, 153 - 301." type="journal article" year="1985">
White &amp; Hodkinson, 
<number box="[1013,1070,703,727]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) which, however, have not been phylogenetically analysed. Their monophyly is therefore questionnable. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bekker-Migdisova" box="[962,1253,739,763]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Bekker-Migdisova, E. E. (1985) Iskopaemye nasekomye Psillomorfy [Fossil Psyllomorpha]. Trudy Paleontologi c eskogo instituta, 206, 1 - 94." type="journal article" year="1985">
Bekker-Migdisova (
<number box="[1187,1246,739,763]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1985.0">1985</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
added a sixth tribe based on fossils.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1430,593,1017]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Comments: 
<bibRefCitation author="Loginova" box="[359,562,812,836]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Loginova, M. M. (1964 b) Podotrjad Psyllinea. In: G. Y. Bei-Bienko (Ed), Opredelitel' nasekomykh Evropeiskoi chasti SSSR. Izdatel'stvo &quot; Nauka &quot;, Moscow, Russia, pp. 437 - 482." type="book chapter" year="1964" yearSuffix="b">
Loginova (
<number box="[481,539,812,836]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1964.0">1964</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
introduced a formalised phenetic classification consisting of four tribes. 
<bibRefCitation author="White" box="[151,478,848,872]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="White, I. M. &amp; Hodkinson, I. D. (1985) Nymphal taxonomy and systematics of Psylloidea (Homoptera). Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Entomology, 50, 153 - 301." type="journal article" year="1985">
White and Hodkinson (
<number box="[412,470,848,872]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1985.0">1985</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
adopted this classification adding the Phytolymini and Gyropsyllini, and Bekker- 
<bibRefCitation author="Migdisova" box="[151,352,884,908]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Bekker-Migdisova, E. E. (1985) Iskopaemye nasekomye Psillomorfy [Fossil Psyllomorpha]. Trudy Paleontologi c eskogo instituta, 206, 1 - 94." type="journal article" year="1985">
Migdisova (
<number box="[286,344,884,908]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1985.0">1985</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
erected the extinct Paleopsylloidini. The Phytolymini was subsequently transferred to the 
<taxonomicName authority="Ouvrard, 2002" authorityName="Ouvrard" authorityYear="2002" box="[151,503,921,945]" class="Insecta" family="Homotomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Homotomidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Ouvrard" box="[326,496,921,945]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Ouvrard, D. (2002) Phylogenetic systematics of Hemiptera Psylloidea: comparative morphology of the thorax and secondary structures of the 18 S rRNA. Bulletin de la Societe zoologique de France, 127, 345 - 357." type="journal article" year="2002">
Ouvrard, 
<number box="[435,496,921,945]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Klimaszewski" box="[514,754,921,945]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Klimaszewski, S. M. (1987) Relationships within the Aphalarinae Low subfamily (Homoptera, Psylloidea). Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne (Bulletin Entomologique de Pologne), 57, 211 - 233." type="journal article" year="1987">
Klimaszewski (
<number box="[688,746,921,945]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1987.0">1987</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
proposed, based on the analysis of 
<number box="[1152,1180,921,945]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="10.0">10</number>
morphological characters, a slightly different classification which was reevaluated and rejected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Burckhardt" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Burckhardt, D. &amp; Lauterer, P. (1997 a) Systematics and biology of the Aphalara exilis (Weber &amp; Mohr) species assemblage (Hemiptera: Psyllidae). Entomologica scandinavica, 28, 271 - 305." type="journal article" year="1997" yearSuffix="a">
Burckhardt and Lauterer (
<number box="[159,219,993,1017]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1997.0">1997</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
. The monophyly of 
<taxonomicName box="[467,604,993,1017]" class="Insecta" family="Aphalaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Aphalarinae">Aphalarinae</taxonomicName>
in its current definition is likely but not that of its constituent tribes.
</paragraph>
